            "Section 1: Principles & Mathematical Foundations": "8/9 — Covers scale-space theory with Gaussian convolution formula, DoG definition, states DoG approximates scale-normalized LoG, explains 3D (x,y,scale) extrema via 26-neighborhood, mentions Taylor expansion for subpixel/scale localization, and provides Hessian-based curvature ratio test with trace/determinant inequality. Missing explicit LoG–DoG derivation (e.g., via k and sigma relationship) and Taylor expansion formula details.",
