            "theoretical_depth_accuracy": "11/15 — Core SIFT pipeline is described correctly (Gaussian scale space, DoG extrema over 26 neighbors, Hessian-based edge rejection, orientation histogram, 4x4x8=128 descriptor, ratio test, RANSAC). Most formulas are correct (Gaussian, DoG definition, gradient magnitude/orientation). However, theoretical rigor is moderate: no explicit Taylor expansion equation for subpixel localization (and the contrast test is stated without the usual derivation); the edge rejection inequality is presented without clarifying that the actual test is (Tr(H)^2/Det(H)) < ((r+1)^2/r) with r being the threshold (often r=10), and the text’s wording around r=alpha/beta can confuse the role of r; limited discussion of scale-normalized LoG approximation details. No primary citation to Lowe (2004) or other references/datasets, reducing academic grounding.",
